    </div>

    <p>The anxiolytic properties of reishi are attributed to its triterpene compounds, particularly ganoderic acids A, B, C, and D. These molecules cross the blood-brain barrier and enhance GABA-A receptor sensitivity, producing a calming effect that multiple clinical and preclinical studies have documented. Unlike synthetic anxiolytics, triterpenes do not cause dependence or withdrawal symptoms at supplemental doses.</p>

    <div class="info-cards">
